<refentry id="glGetPolygonStipple.3G">
	<refmeta id="glGetPolygonStipple.3G-meta">
		<refentrytitle>glGetPolygonStipple</refentrytitle>
		<manvolnum>3G</manvolnum>
	</refmeta>
	<refnamediv id="glGetPolygonStipple.3G-name">
		<refname>glGetPolygonStipple</refname>
		<refpurpose>return the polygon stipple pattern</refpurpose>
	</refnamediv>
	<refsynopsisdiv id="glGetPolygonStipple.3G-c_spec">
		<title>C Specification</title>
		<funcsynopsis>
			<funcprototype>
				<funcdef>void&nbsp;<function>glGetPolygonStipple</function></funcdef>
				<paramdef>GLubyte&nbsp;*<parameter>mask</parameter></paramdef>
			</funcprototype>
		</funcsynopsis>
	</refsynopsisdiv>
	<refsect1 id="glGetPolygonStipple.3G-parameters">
		<title>Parameters</title>
		<variablelist>
			<varlistentry>
				<term><parameter>mask</parameter></term>
				<listitem>
					<simpara>
						Returns the stipple pattern. The initial value is all 1's.
					</simpara>
				</listitem>
			</varlistentry>
		</variablelist>
	</refsect1>
	<refsect1 id="glGetPolygonStipple.3G-description">
		<title>Description</title>
		<para>
			<function>glGetPolygonStipple</function> returns to <parameter>mask</parameter> a <inlineequation>
				<mml:math>
					<mml:mrow>
						<mml:mn>32</mml:mn>
						<mml:mo>&times;</mml:mo>
						<mml:mn>32</mml:mn>
					</mml:mrow>
				</mml:math>
			</inlineequation> polygon stipple pattern. The pattern is packed into memory as if <function
			moreinfo="refentry">glReadPixels</function> with both <parameter>height</parameter> and <parameter>width</parameter> of
			32, <parameter>type</parameter> of <constant>GL_BITMAP</constant>, and <parameter>format</parameter> of
			<constant>GL_COLOR_INDEX</constant> were called, and the stipple pattern were stored in an internal <inlineequation>
				<mml:math>
					<mml:mrow>
						<mml:mn>32</mml:mn>
						<mml:mo>&times;</mml:mo>
						<mml:mn>32</mml:mn>
					</mml:mrow>
				</mml:math>
			</inlineequation> color index buffer. Unlike <function moreinfo="refentry">glReadPixels</function>, however, pixel
			transfer operations (shift, offset, pixel map) are not applied to the returned stipple image.
		</para>
	</refsect1>
	<refsect1 id="glGetPolygonStipple.3G-notes">
		<title>Notes</title>
		<para>
			If an error is generated, no change is made to the contents of <parameter>mask</parameter>.
		</para>
	</refsect1>
	<refsect1 id="glGetPolygonStipple.3G-errors">
		<title>Errors</title>
		<para>
			<constant>GL_INVALID_OPERATION</constant> is generated if <function>glGetPolygonStipple</function> is executed between
			the execution of <function moreinfo="refentry">glBegin</function> and the corresponding execution of <function
			moreinfo="refentry">glEnd</function>.
		</para>
	</refsect1>
